    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-02-07T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-02-07T16:00:00-05:00" n="261"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d261">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">833.73/39: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-02-07T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 7, 1922—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 8—9:47 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8. Referring to the Department’s number 2, February 4, 7 p.m.<note n="44"
                        xml:id="d261fn44">See footnote 40, <ref target="#pg_518">p.
                        518</ref>.</note> Western Telegraph Company today presented to the Uruguayan
                    Minister of Industry a communication embodying resolution of London company,
                    also handing me copy as arranged. I am to be informed of the Government’s reply
                    and shall telegraph answer at once; meanwhile, I am in close touch with the
                    manager of the All America Cables.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Armour</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
